China's GDP grew 3 percent year on year to over 121 trillion yuan ($17.93 trillion) in 2022 despite various pressures. There are expectations for growth to reach 5 percent or higher in 2023. The three driving forces of China's economy – investment, exports, and domestic consumption – are all set to gather momentum in 2023. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Kate Kui explains.